                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d675">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terres</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-12-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 16, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Terres reports the arrival of General Nord on December 16; that great
                    excitement prevails; that shooting is going on in the city; that serious trouble
                    is expected; that the Haitian secretary of the interior, with general police, is
                    at the United States legation.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
